[DhtmlXQ_comment0]mg tactics zugzwang 03||Game adapted from <<??????>> by ???||This is an actual midgame situation played in competition.||Both sides have exactly the same material but red has the obvious advantage with the central cannon and the horse and chariot geared to attack black's left plan.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
[DhtmlXQ_comment10]Black protects the horse ...||Black does not want to be pinned by protecting the horse with R8=7.[/DhtmlXQ_comment10]
[DhtmlXQ_comment13]Up till this stage, red has successfully used one chariot to tie up black's 3 major pieces. ||With this cannon move, material can be gained.||If the chariot runs away, the horse is lost.[/DhtmlXQ_comment13]
[DhtmlXQ_comment17]Black resigns after losing the cannon.||Red threatens to take the pawn, further improving his material advantage. If black moved R8+1 to protect the side pawn, Red would answer with a fork of H4+3.||If black chose to attack with H6+5, red would take the side pawn and then move the chariot to the other side for a discover check. ||The huge advantage goes to red. And all this was possible because of the zugzwang cannon move at move number 7.[/DhtmlXQ_comment17]
